General Development Rules

Error Handling:
1. Always create custom error types
2. Always log errors with context
3. Never expose internal errors to client
4. Always use structured logging

Testing:
1. Always write unit tests for services and repositories
2. Always use testify for assertions
3. Always mock external dependencies
4. Never test implementation details

Documentation:
1. Always document public functions and types
2. Always include examples in documentation
3. Always maintain API documentation with swagger

Performance:
1. Always use indexes for MongoDB queries
2. Always implement proper pagination
3. Always use connection pooling
4. Never fetch all records without pagination

